1
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:51,040
Where did Sarai disappear to?

2
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,719
You know this woman?

3
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:04,880
A life must be repaid with a life.

4
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:08,520
No, Sarai. Don't.

5
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,359
Sarai...

6
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,959
<i>Who is Sarai?</i>

7
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:16,040
Would you mind telling me about her?

8
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:24,000
All my life, I knew my father
had never been a good man.

9
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:28,920
But I never thought
he could do something like this.

10
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,800
I'll go talk to him.

11
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:35,800
Wait.

12
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:46,960
What are you doing?

13
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,360
I didn't want you to go.

14
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:51,400
Why?

15
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:54,919
If your father really
had something to do with Sarai's death,

16
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:56,880
you could be in danger.

17
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:03,480
You're worried about me?

18
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:06,760
Yes.

19
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,800
No need to rush.

20
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:17,240
I promise.

21
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,879
You promise not to act rashly, right?

22
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:21,880
I promise I won't tell anyone

23
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,360
you're very heavy.

24
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:38,440
Thank you
for bringing me back to my senses.

25
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:43,160
Promise me
you won't act rashly like that again.

26
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:47,280
We'll investigate this together,
as carefully as possible.

27
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,400
I promise.

28
00:04:56,120 --> 00:05:00,039
We'll help each other
seek justice for Sarai calmly

29
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,440
and sensibly.

30
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,360
So it's you.

31
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,560
Nice place.

32
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:36,120
No wonder Mr. Phum hides you here.

33
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,000
Sister.

34
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:53,080
So you're cornered enough
to call me sister now?

35
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:59,360
Even if you called me mother,
I still wouldn't spare you today.

36
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,560
You shameless woman!

37
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:18,680
Ow!

38
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,600
You dare slap me?

39
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,240
Yes.

40
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,600
I've put up with you for long enough.

41
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,839
I'm going to tell Mr. Phum.

42
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:44,200
Go ahead.

43
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:48,960
Then we'll see who Mr. Phum listens to,

44
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,760
you or me.

45
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,000
You're more vicious than I thought.

46
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,520
Leave

47
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:17,880
before I change my mind and kill you.

48
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,080
You still don't what I'm capable of.

49
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:13,119
I already told you.
We can't go to Skull Island right now.

50
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:16,519
<i>I have another job for you.
Easy work, quick pay.</i>

51
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:17,439
<i>Interested?</i>

52
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,600
What job?

53
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,120
Win!

54
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:15,600
Pat, why are you so startled?

55
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:18,160
And why are you here?

56
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:21,400
Win, look at that.

57
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,200
There's nothing there.

58
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:41,440
Pat, you still haven't answered me.

59
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,520
Why did you come here?

60
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,360
I came to look at this photo.

61
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:54,000
Hey, Pat.

62
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:56,279
Honestly,

63
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:59,760
I don't see what's beautiful
about this Black Coral photo.

64
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:01,600
It looks terrifying.

65
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:05,200
But it's worth an enormous fortune.

66
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:09,920
What?

67
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,800
The black jewel of the sea.

68
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,000
People say it really exists.

69
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:22,360
At first, I didn't believe it.

70
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:24,760
But once I saw this photo,

71
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:28,800
I decided I had to find it.

72
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:33,000
Are you going to help me?

73
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:42,880
And what will I get in return?

74
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:52,320
You already know what you'll get.

75
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,120
Sairung.

76
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:41,800
Why won't you turn around?

77
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:46,800
- I'm in a hurry.
- I said turn around.

78
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:51,880
Turn around right now.

79
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,320
What happened to your face?

80
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:06,080
It looks like
you got into a fight with someone.

81
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:12,440
If I tell you, please don't scold me.

82
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:14,200
What did you do?

83
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:21,680
Last night, I went to a party.

84
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:24,520
I drank too much,
so I got into a fight with a friend.

85
00:13:25,560 --> 00:13:27,599
I think you have far too much free time.

86
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:29,960
Try doing something useful for once.

87
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:33,080
You're wasting time on nonsense.

88
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:45,160
I'm going to do something meaningful,
just like you want.

89
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:17,720
The details
and half the money are in here.

90
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:21,680
Finish the job,
and you can come collect the rest.

91
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,200
What's this?

92
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,160
What the hell?

93
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:21,600
What is it?

94
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:48,240
It's nothing.

95
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,800
What the hell is wrong with my brain?

96
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,560
What are you doing in here?

97
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:02,760
I asked what you're doing in this room.

98
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:05,879
Why can't I be here?

99
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:07,639
I ordered that no one come in.

100
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:08,919
Then why did you come in?

101
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:10,319
Get out.

102
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:13,839
Why?

103
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:17,520
Are you afraid I'll find something?

104
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:20,200
What are you talking about?

105
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:23,000
Stop pretending, Dad.

106
00:17:24,119 --> 00:17:25,520
I know that...

107
00:17:26,040 --> 00:17:27,400
What do you know?

108
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,360
I know

109
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:34,239
you're still the same man
you've always been.

110
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:36,039
What are you talking about?

111
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:38,400
Because of your womanizing.

112
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:41,040
Because you found someone new
and forgot the old one.

113
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:43,920
That's why Sarai was heartbroken

114
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:47,800
and ran away. Isn't that right?

115
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:50,560
Of course.

116
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:54,079
In your eyes,
I will always be a terrible father.

117
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:55,959
But know one thing.

118
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:59,400
This terrible father
loves you more than anything,

119
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:01,960
whether you believe it or not.

120
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:21,760
You did the right thing
by not saying anything.

121
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:25,040
I understand how you feel.

122
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:27,479
I want to see you too,

123
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:30,080
but no one is home right now.

124
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,679
Na has gone out to sea,

125
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:35,320
and Dad and Mom went to a party.
They'll probably be home late.

126
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:44,759
How about this? Come see me at my house.

127
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:47,800
I'll make something delicious for you.

128
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:51,720
Okay. See you soon.

129
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,040
You really made this yourself?

130
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:09,960
I don't want to brag. Try it first.

131
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:12,560
Alright.

132
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:28,080
How was it?

133
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:32,720
Are you sure this is really spaghetti?

134
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:36,720
Why?

135
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:39,000
Try it.

136
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:00,760
It's good.

137
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:06,360
Who said it wasn't?

138
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,800
You're really something.

139
00:20:13,560 --> 00:20:15,279
So what did you put in this?

140
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:16,960
It's really delicious.

141
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:20,560
My heart.

142
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:28,880
You have to pay attention
from the step of boiling the pasta.

143
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:35,640
You tricked me into getting happy again.

144
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:39,520
Well, you tricked me first.

145
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:42,000
So now we're even.

146
00:20:42,840 --> 00:20:45,200
Eat before it gets cold.

147
00:20:58,080 --> 00:21:01,680
Can you eat shrimp?

148
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:05,280
Why?

149
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:09,840
Because you're a conservationist.

150
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:14,360
You should know

151
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,080
I can eat shrimp.

152
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:02,080
What are you smiling at?

153
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:08,160
I didn't expect you
to be such a homemaker.

154
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:12,160
You've misunderstood.

155
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:16,159
Na says I can only be

156
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:18,000
a house ghost.

157
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:27,000
I'm glad to see you're less stressed now.

158
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:38,400
I feel confused
every time I talk to my father.

159
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:44,200
Sometimes he acts like
he knows something about Sarai's death.

160
00:22:45,320 --> 00:22:47,720
But other times,
he acts like he knows nothing at all.

161
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:53,719
This case seems very complicated.

162
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:55,920
You need to stay calm.

163
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:03,480
I'm trying.

164
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:13,320
Dad.

165
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:18,760
Hello.

166
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:29,720
We need to talk. Please come with me.

167
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,480
I'm sorry

168
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:00,080
for coming to see Kaimook
without asking for permission first.

169
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:08,759
But

170
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:12,880
I give you my word as a man.
I haven't done anything improper,

171
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:16,440
and I will never do anything to damage...

172
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:24,360
the woman I love.

173
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,800
Are you telling me

174
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,000
you love my daughter?

175
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:50,120
Yes.

176
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:53,240
I love Kaimook.

177
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:03,160
Good. Then this will be easier.

178
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:09,480
If you really love Kaimook,
you wouldn't want the woman you love

179
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:11,680
to be in danger, would you?

180
00:25:13,640 --> 00:25:16,120
Of course not.

181
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:23,400
I don't want Kaimook
to intern at SAVE SEA anymore.

182
00:25:25,880 --> 00:25:29,360
You saw what happened to my daughter.

183
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:31,480
She almost didn't make it out alive.

184
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:36,559
So if you love Kaimook,
you should help support her decision

185
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:38,520
to leave SAVE SEA.

186
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:41,719
Dad,

187
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:43,040
- but I have to--
- I know.

188
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:46,000
I've already contacted
another place for you.

189
00:25:46,520 --> 00:25:49,040
I guarantee their organization
is just as large as SAVE SEA.

190
00:25:58,920 --> 00:26:00,040
I'm counting on you.

191
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:28,479
Dad,

192
00:26:28,480 --> 00:26:31,200
my internship at SAVE SEA
is very important to me.

193
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:35,480
I know you need a portfolio
to apply for your master's degree.

194
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:38,320
It's not just that.

195
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:41,000
I want to be part of an organization

196
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:45,880
that really helps conserve
and restore damaged natural resources.

197
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:52,880
And SAVE SEA is the only place
that aligns with what I want.

198
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:55,719
That place is full of trouble,

199
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:57,119
both human and ghostly.

200
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:59,960
I can't let you intern there again.

201
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:04,760
Dad, please.

202
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:06,320
Mook,

203
00:27:06,840 --> 00:27:08,520
I've let you have your way in everything.

204
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:10,559
But this time, no.

205
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:12,199
I'm not doing this

206
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:15,680
for myself. I'm doing this for you.

207
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:19,680
- But Dad.
- Mook,

208
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:22,199
stay calm.

209
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:26,360
He's in strict-father mode right now.
Don't row a boat against the current yet.

210
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:29,480
I'll handle it.

211
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:32,760
Don't worry. Trust me.

212
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:35,000
Yes, Mom.

213
00:27:58,160 --> 00:27:58,959
Dear.

214
00:27:58,960 --> 00:28:01,280
Mook's getting more stubborn
the older she gets.

215
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,840
Someone must be stirring her up.

216
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:07,200
Don't blame other people.

217
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:09,919
Our daughter is stubborn just like you.

218
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:12,640
Oh? Why would you say that?

219
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:14,600
Isn't it true?

220
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:18,599
She got
that conservationist blood from you.

221
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:22,440
You're the one who instilled
these things in her since she was little.

222
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:25,199
Now she's following in your footsteps.

223
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:28,359
But all of a sudden,
you're trying to stop her.

224
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:30,360
Isn't that a little dictatorial?

225
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:33,040
Hold on.

226
00:28:34,120 --> 00:28:37,240
So now worrying about my daughter
makes me a dictator?

227
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:40,199
Worrying so much

228
00:28:40,200 --> 00:28:42,840
that you refuse to listen
to your daughter's opinion,

229
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:45,680
if that isn't dictatorial,
what would you call it?

230
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:50,560
Mook will never understand
that kind of concern.

231
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:55,520
What should I do?

232
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:59,280
Meet her halfway.

233
00:29:31,360 --> 00:29:34,439
"Right now, shallow coral reefs
in the Gulf of Thailand

234
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:37,479
have been damaged
and greatly reduced in number."

235
00:29:37,480 --> 00:29:40,120
"This has caused
harmful effects to the ecosystem."

236
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:43,759
"Shallow coral reefs
are extremely important,

237
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:47,199
whether as habitats
for aquatic animals and marine fish,

238
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,559
or in helping reduce the force of waves

239
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:53,400
and preventing coastal erosion."

240
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:16,199
I don't see what's beautiful

241
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:18,039
about this Black Coral photo.

242
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:19,400
It looks terrifying.

243
00:30:20,600 --> 00:30:23,280
But it's worth an enormous fortune.

244
00:30:26,760 --> 00:30:27,720
What?

245
00:30:29,040 --> 00:30:31,600
The black jewel of the sea.

246
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:34,080
People say it really exists.

247
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:40,160
At first, I didn't believe it.

248
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:42,600
But once I saw this photo,

249
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:46,680
I decided I had to find it.

250
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:21,640
Who's that?

251
00:33:25,280 --> 00:33:26,240
Go.

252
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:34,240
Miss.

253
00:33:35,440 --> 00:33:37,640
Miss. Excuse me.

254
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:41,960
What are you doing out here in the dark?

255
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:46,560
Miss.

256
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:56,599
I asked, what are you doing here?

257
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:59,880
There was a man
sneaking around behind you.

258
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:02,519
I think you should go home.

259
00:34:02,520 --> 00:34:03,880
I can escort you.

260
00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:09,800
No need. I live in the condo right here.

261
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:30,400
What? Such an easy job,
and you still managed to fail.

262
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:34,560
Don't contact me again. If anything
comes up, I'll contact you myself.

263
00:34:35,639 --> 00:34:36,719
Useless.

264
00:34:41,800 --> 00:34:42,639
Oh!

265
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:45,120
Mr. Phum?

266
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:56,000
Hey. Mr. Phum.

267
00:34:56,639 --> 00:34:57,840
Mr. Phum.

268
00:35:01,920 --> 00:35:02,880
Pong?

269
00:35:04,080 --> 00:35:05,320
Who's he?

270
00:35:08,720 --> 00:35:09,799
Mr. Phum.

271
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:11,640
I asked. Who is he?

272
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:14,079
Well...

273
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:15,280
No, Mr. Phum, don't.

274
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:19,880
<i>The number that you've dialed
cannot be connected at this time.</i>

275
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:25,680
Who is he?

276
00:35:28,840 --> 00:35:30,440
Just a friend of mine.

277
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:33,880
Don't let me find out
that you're planning something vile.

278
00:35:37,040 --> 00:35:39,640
I'm not like your beloved Sarai.

279
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:45,000
Ever since she cheated on you,
you see everyone in the worst light.

280
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:48,680
How many times have I told you
not to say that name again?

281
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:51,080
Fine.

282
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:53,439
Then I'll talk about that Pakarang woman

283
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:55,760
you're keeping at the condo.

284
00:35:56,520 --> 00:35:58,680
Whatever I do has nothing to do with you.

285
00:35:59,920 --> 00:36:01,600
Do not mess with Pakarang.

286
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:04,080
Otherwise, don't say I didn't warn you.

287
00:36:43,120 --> 00:36:44,600
It's raining today.

288
00:36:47,600 --> 00:36:48,600
Yes.

289
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:53,680
But it doesn't rain every day,

290
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:55,960
does it?

291
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:00,240
Yes. You're right.

292
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:03,360
There are still plenty
of good-weather days.

293
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:06,880
So,

294
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:10,720
no matter how heavy the rain is,

295
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:12,760
or how strong the storm gets,

296
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:15,120
we'll walk through it together.

297
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:16,840
Okay?

298
00:37:19,240 --> 00:37:20,240
Okay.

299
00:37:35,040 --> 00:37:36,119
Thank you very much.

300
00:37:36,120 --> 00:37:37,320
It's no problem.

301
00:37:38,240 --> 00:37:39,280
Dad.

302
00:37:44,120 --> 00:37:45,000
Dad.

303
00:37:46,400 --> 00:37:47,280
Hello.

304
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:51,200
I'm heading back now.

305
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:59,360
You're very lucky to have a father
who loves and understands you.

306
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:01,000
That's really rare.

307
00:38:03,040 --> 00:38:04,520
What do you mean?

308
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:12,080
Dad.

309
00:38:19,960 --> 00:38:23,480
Thank you so much, Dad,
for understanding me.

310
00:38:24,120 --> 00:38:25,600
I love you the most.

311
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:32,120
Hey.

312
00:38:33,120 --> 00:38:34,839
But you must promise

313
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:38,200
to follow the conditions
I asked Mr. Don for.

314
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:42,799
Yes. I promise not to go off-site.

315
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:45,200
I'll intern only inside the company.

316
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:50,680
Good. Then that's settled.
We meet halfway.

317
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:55,640
But why did you suddenly change your mind?

318
00:38:57,080 --> 00:39:00,600
Because I didn't want your mom
to call me a dictator.

319
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:02,560
Mom?

320
00:39:03,640 --> 00:39:06,080
Yeah. Your mom worries about you

321
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:09,040
just as much as I do.

322
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:14,360
I know. I love you and Mom the most.

323
00:39:17,960 --> 00:39:21,640
Do your best in your internship.
I'm leaving.

324
00:39:22,920 --> 00:39:24,160
Yes, sir.

325
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:37,559
Welcome back to your internship.

326
00:39:37,560 --> 00:39:38,600
Thank you.

327
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:50,040
So this is
what the sky looks like after the rain.

328
00:40:06,680 --> 00:40:08,120
Is something wrong?

329
00:40:09,560 --> 00:40:11,200
Are you thinking about Sarai?

330
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:19,320
Or did you find out something new?

331
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:29,640
I'm not like your beloved Sarai.

332
00:40:30,680 --> 00:40:35,120
Ever since she cheated on you,
you see everyone in the worst light.

333
00:40:36,160 --> 00:40:39,200
You once told me Sarai was innocent.

334
00:40:40,640 --> 00:40:43,680
More importantly,
she loved Mr. Phum very much.

335
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:47,800
I don't think a woman like that
would have an affair.

336
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:53,840
I don't want to believe it either.

337
00:40:55,880 --> 00:40:58,400
Could it have been a misunderstanding?

338
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:02,240
A man like my father
would never believe something easily

339
00:41:03,160 --> 00:41:05,960
without evidence,
or without seeing it with his own eyes.

340
00:41:06,720 --> 00:41:11,240
So you think Mr. Phum
might be involved in Sarai's death

341
00:41:12,120 --> 00:41:13,960
because he was angry with her over this.

342
00:41:16,760 --> 00:41:19,360
Sarai tried to communicate with me,

343
00:41:20,080 --> 00:41:23,760
probably to ask me for help.
If my father wasn't involved,

344
00:41:24,440 --> 00:41:26,600
she should have communicated
with him instead.

345
00:41:27,120 --> 00:41:28,520
Don't you think so?

346
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:32,359
But before we have evidence,

347
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:34,480
I don't want you to jump to conclusions.

348
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:37,880
Because if it isn't what we think,

349
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:41,920
you'll be committing a sin.

350
00:41:46,160 --> 00:41:48,560
Then I must have
been sinning for a long time.

351
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:51,720
Because I've never felt good
about my father,

352
00:41:53,960 --> 00:41:55,800
ever since he caused my mother's death.

353
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:03,480
Why couldn't I have a father
who does good things,

354
00:42:04,040 --> 00:42:05,920
like other people's fathers?

355
00:42:25,720 --> 00:42:28,120
This is the sea around Skull Island.

356
00:42:31,360 --> 00:42:33,280
You know Skull Island?

357
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:39,480
No.

358
00:42:40,160 --> 00:42:41,960
Did I say that?

359
00:42:43,120 --> 00:42:47,560
Try to think carefully.
Maybe you're from around there.

360
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:55,240
I...

361
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:57,640
I can't remember.

362
00:42:58,160 --> 00:42:59,280
Uh...

363
00:43:01,720 --> 00:43:04,759
If you can't remember yet,
don't force yourself.

364
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:06,400
You'll just get a headache.

365
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:15,160
Well,

366
00:43:15,720 --> 00:43:18,240
I want to remember everything already.

367
00:43:19,320 --> 00:43:21,560
Being idle like this
makes me feel so useless.

368
00:43:23,200 --> 00:43:24,920
Don't be too hard on yourself.

369
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:31,879
How about this?
I'm organizing a photo exhibition.

370
00:43:31,880 --> 00:43:34,680
You can help me,
so you'll have something to do.

371
00:43:36,480 --> 00:43:38,480
But I don't know anything
about photography.

372
00:43:39,560 --> 00:43:41,560
And I don't remember anything,

373
00:43:43,280 --> 00:43:49,080
Who knows. Maybe you're one of the people
who knows the sea best.

374
00:43:59,360 --> 00:44:00,480
Alright, then.

375
00:44:07,640 --> 00:44:08,720
You're so much like her.

376
00:44:10,440 --> 00:44:13,680
Why are you so much like...?

377
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:18,600
Who?

378
00:44:20,040 --> 00:44:21,480
Who do you think I'm like?

379
00:44:26,960 --> 00:44:28,040
It's nothing.

380
00:45:02,960 --> 00:45:04,360
How dare you walk away from me?

381
00:45:09,200 --> 00:45:12,560
It isn't time for him to know

382
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:16,040
who you are yet.

383
00:45:21,920 --> 00:45:24,240
No! No!

384
00:46:03,920 --> 00:46:05,600
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
